  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Problem\nThere are several issues with tx history. See https://github.com/status-im-status-go/issues/1665 and #9203 \n\nCurrently we show \"No transactions in your history\" which is misleading as the issue is that they are not updated. \n\nNew empty state can be shown in this case.\nOther empty states require updating for consistency\n\n## Implementation\n<img width=\"1470\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019-12-20 at 13 50 11\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/71250014-a9f40c80-232f-11ea-87c9-d12c7b3a6ef9.png\">\n\n\nFigma: https://www.figma.com/file/XUehMnhyD1FGcWzvGz6SXqvh/Wallet?node-id=1743%3A303\n\n#### Persistent link\nLet's always show the etherscan link since we are not sure if the history is consistent\n\n#### There might be more. Refresh\nLet's give the user control over refreshing the history.\n\n#### Loading\nSince the loading might take a while, let's show Loading transaction history. This might take a while. below the loading spinner;\n\n#### Error\nDesign should be shown on two requests:\n* Verify that there were transactions\n* Exclude received tokens\n@rasom can you clarify why we need to exclude these?\n\n#### No transactions\nFix the line-height of No transactions here yet (Should be Main Text 15px style)\n\nEtherscan link should include address of selected account (i.e. the account in view): https://etherscan.io/address/address\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\nPixel perfect according design\n\n## Future Steps\n* Add account\n* Send funds from one account to another\n* Check History\n\n\nNote for post-v.1 : Let's keep in mind that there's more to improve this screen. For instance, loading of long transaction history lists should be paginated and additional Send/Receive buttons should appear.",
